@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Filtered Lookup in Detail Dialog";
}

@section ContentHeader {
    <h1>@ViewBag.Title<small></small></h1>
}

<div class="alert alert-info alert-dismissable">
    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
    <p>A frequently asked question is how to pass some data from master dialog to a lookup editor
    in a detail dialog to filter items.</p>
    <p>In this sample we have a custom Order dialog that has a Product Category selection.</p>
    <p>When you click Add button in Order Details grid, Product editor in detail dialog will 
    only show products in selected Category.</p>
    <p>To achieve this, we need to flow selected category information on this route: Master Order Dialog -&gt;
       Order Detail Grid Editor -&gt; Order Detail Dialog -&gt; Product Lookup Editor.
    
    <p style="text-align: right;"><b>Source Files:</b> 
        @Html.SereneSource("Index.cshtml"), 
        @Html.SereneSource("FilteredLookupInDetailForm.cs")
        @Html.SereneSource("FilteredLookupInDetailGrid.ts")
        @Html.SereneSource("FilteredLookupInDetailDialog.ts")
        @Html.SereneSource("FilteredLookupDetailEditor.ts")
        @Html.SereneSource("FilteredLookupOrderDetailDialog.ts")
    </p>
</div>

<div id="GridDiv"></div>

<script type="text/javascript">
    jQuery(function () {
        new Serene.BasicSamples.FilteredLookupInDetailGrid($('#GridDiv'), {}).init();

        Q.initFullHeightGridPage($('#GridDiv'));
    });
</script>